page.title: 14Housing
page.content: The housing varies from 25% council housing with well laid out bungalows and houses with large gardens,to large stone houses, about 5%, dating back 80-100 years.There is approxiamately 10% of cob-stone walled, thatched cottages. Ribbon development usually bungalows-the occassional house-and one terraced row of houses has taken place over the last 50 years and this constitutes the remaining 60% of housing,stretching along the edge of the two minor roads whose intersection in front of the church produces the Village Square.
